Deliverables
Backend server code with setup instructions (including how to run on laptop and, optionally, deploy to free host).

Android app source code (Android Studio project).

API documentation (simple README with endpoint details).

Database schema (SQL dump or migration scripts).

Instructions for initial setup: creating the first admin user (Omar) and adding other users.

Notes
Prioritise core functionality first: authentication, adding invoices with items/consumers, and balance calculation.

The undo feature can be implemented using a soft‑delete with a timestamp and a background job that permanently deletes after 10 seconds (or simply a timer on the client that shows undo option and calls an API to restore).

Make sure all sensitive data (passwords) are hashed on the server.

The app should handle multiple users concurrently; the server must manage state correctly.